         <abstract>
            <p>We consider the heat equation u&lt;sub&gt;t&lt;/sub&gt; = u&lt;sub&gt;xx&lt;/sub&gt; in the quarter-plane x ≥ 0, t ≥ 0 with initial condition u(x, 0) = f(x) and boundary condition α u(0, t) + u&lt;sub&gt;x&lt;/sub&gt;(0, t) = 0. We are concerned with the stability of difference approximations v&lt;sub&gt;ν&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;sup&gt;n + 1&lt;/sup&gt; = Qv&lt;sub&gt;ν&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt; to this problem. Using the resolvent operator (Q - zI)&lt;sup&gt;-1&lt;/sup&gt;, we give sufficient conditions for consistent, one-step explicit schemes to be stable in the maximum norm.</p>
          </abstract>
